<org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmi:id="-V7INE-r4pWlTo1PEbFT_Pg" name="def_criteria,_rIrNgJjUEd6JmoH2XFiafA" guid="-V7INE-r4pWlTo1PEbFT_Pg" changeDate="2009-10-26T10:52:54.656-0700" version="7.5.0">
  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    In order to identify the best solution from a set of candidate solutions, assessment criteria need to be identified.&#xD;
    Meaningful assessment criteria are established in collaboration with stakeholders and a team representing all relevant&#xD;
    areas of expertise. Typically, the assessment criteria are based upon customer constraints, required performance&#xD;
    characteristics, and/or costs.&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
  <sections xmi:id="_TQ90sMJZEd6Ame-XMnb0Gg" name="Identify Key Performance Parameters (KPP)" guid="_TQ90sMJZEd6Ame-XMnb0Gg">
    <sectionDescription>Identify a set of KPPs for the scope under investigation. KPPs are objective measures of performance and typically relate&#xD;
to quality of service, reliability, tolerances of accuracy, and specific constraints relating to size or mass.</sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_bTzpwMJZEd6Ame-XMnb0Gg" name="Identify stakeholder requirements" guid="_bTzpwMJZEd6Ame-XMnb0Gg">
    <sectionDescription>Identify the applicable stakeholder requirements for the area covered by the proposed solutions.</sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_lesJYMJZEd6Ame-XMnb0Gg" name="Translate KPPs and stakeholder requirements into assessment criteria" guid="_lesJYMJZEd6Ame-XMnb0Gg">
    <sectionDescription>Determine appropriate assessment criteria based on the KPPs and stakeholder requirements identified in the previous steps.&#xD;
Assessment criteria normally are subjective but can also be very specific. A subjective target could be low cost. A&#xD;
specific target could be a precise measure of accuracy i.e. +/- 0.1 mm.</sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_o4iaEMJZEd6Ame-XMnb0Gg" name="Create or update the Trade Study Report" guid="_o4iaEMJZEd6Ame-XMnb0Gg">
    <sectionDescription>Capture the assessment criteria in the Trade Study Report.</sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <purpose>Precondition for the selection of an optimum realization of a&amp;nbsp;candidate solution&amp;nbsp;is the definition of relevant&#xD;
assessment criteria.</purpose>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
